        "id": 253514,
        "name": "",
        "username": "DirkPitt1",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/d/74df32/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2024-10-13T10:02:33.520Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"vegaldn\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"64208\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/vegaldn/48/49147_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> vegaldn:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Why does Signal choose to delete messages from the servers after delivery instead of storing them encrypted?</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Storage space mostly. And donâ€™t collect anything that isnâ€™t necessary policy.</p>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"vegaldn\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"64208\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/vegaldn/48/49147_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> vegaldn:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>What is the privacy risk if messages remain encrypted and the keys are never sent to the server?</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Thereâ€™s an issue of collect now decrypt later. Basically if an attacker could gain access to encrypted messages they could collect it and store until they could decrypt them (getting your encryption keys, through some new form of attack leveraging some newly discovered flaws in cryptographic primitives/protocols or their implementation, or when computing power increases enough for brute forcing encrypted messages be feasible).</p>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"vegaldn\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"64208\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/vegaldn/48/49147_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> vegaldn:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p><strong>How does syncing work in Signal?</strong> Since messages are not stored on the server, where does the new device get them from?</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>At the moment newly linked devices donâ€™t sync message history. Main clients can import local backups.</p>",
